<rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Theatre</rs>: stage area</rs>
<rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList">Theatre</rs> proskenion frieze. Inscribed on the blocks which make up the cornice, of the Doric order, above the inscription of Zoilos, across the back of the Theatre stage. The blocks have simple moulding above, supporting water spouts in the form of lions' heads; the underside has a decoration of mutules. </rs>
<rs type="lastLocation">Findspot: reassembled and restored along the front of the proskenion, next to 565 (which, despite the assembly marks, may be correct).</rs>
</p>
